author: Sammy Batten - Staff writer
title: College football: Saturday's Big 5 matchups
text:
College football: Saturday's Big 5 matchups By Sammy Batten - Staff writer 
Duke (4-1) at Army (1-4) 
Time: Noon. TV: CBSSN 
The bulletin board: The Blue Devils are looking their 13th nonconference victory in the last 14 tries. ... Duke holds a slight 11-10-1 edge against Army. ... Defense and special teams have propelled Duke. The Blue Devils are fifth nationally in scoring defense and ninth in total defense. ... Duke safety Jeremy Cash leads the defense with 9.5 tackles for loss. ... Safety DeVon Edwards has returned kickoffs 95 and 100 yards this year for touchdowns. ... Army’s four losses are by a total of 16 points. ... The Cadets are averaging 287.8 yards rushing. 
East Carolina (3-2) at BYU (3-2) 
Time: 7:30 p.m. TV: ESPNU 
The bulletin board: ECU closes its nonconference schedule as BYU’s homecoming foe — the first meeting between the schools. ... The Pirates have won two straight, led by junior QB James Summers. He rushed for 254 yards and four touchdowns and passed for 263 yards and three scores over the last two games. ... BYU QB Trevor Mangum completed 35 of 53 passes for 365 yards and two scores in last week’s win over Connecticut. 
Wake (2-3, 0-2) at Boston College (3-2, 0-2) 
Time: 3 p.m. TV: Fox Carolinas 
The bulletin board: Both teams are seeking their first ACC victory. ... The Eagles lead the series, 12-8-2, and have won the last two against the Deacs. ... Wake had more rushing and passing yards than Florida State last week in a narrow loss to the Seminoles. Deacs tight end Cam Serigne had 10 catches for 83 yards and a touchdown. ... Boston College leads the ACC in scoring defense (8.0).
